## Overview

This file is the single source of truth for the project's visual identity. Every UI surface — landing pages, dashboards, marketing site, mobile app — derives its tokens from the YAML front-matter above and respects the rationale below. Coding agents read this file before generating any frontend code.

## Colors

The palette is rooted in high-contrast neutrals with a single evocative accent.

- **Primary (#1A1C1E):** Deep ink for headlines and core text. Permanence and readability.
- **Secondary (#6C7278):** Slate for utility — borders, captions, metadata. Never competes with primary.
- **Tertiary (#3B82F6):** Reserved for interaction — primary CTAs, links, focus rings. Use sparingly.
- **Neutral (#F8F9FA):** Page background. Softer than pure white; warmer light reflectance.
- **Error (#DC2626):** Reserved for state semantics. Do not repurpose for branding.

Contrast: every color used as text must hit WCAG AA (≥4.5:1 for body, ≥3:1 for large text).

## Typography

Two families: **Public Sans** for narrative weight, **Inter** for body and UI chrome.

- **Headlines (h1, h2):** Public Sans semi-bold. Institutional, trustworthy, generous x-height.
- **Body (body-md):** Inter regular at 16px. Optimized for screen readability across densities.
- **Labels (label-sm):** Inter medium at 13px for metadata, captions, form helpers.

Line-height contracts upward as size grows (1.1 for h1, 1.6 for body) — deliberate hierarchy signal.

## Layout

Strict 8px grid. Every spacing token is a multiple of 4px. Page max-width: `min(1280px, 92vw)`.

Section vertical rhythm: `xl` (32px) between top-level sections, `lg` (24px) within a section.

## Elevation & Depth

Depth is conveyed through tonal layers and borders, not heavy shadows. Default surface sits on neutral background; elevated surfaces use pure white with a subtle border (1px secondary at 12% opacity).

## Shapes

Architectural softness — `md` (8px) for buttons, inputs, cards. `lg` (12px) for hero panels. `full` reserved for avatars and pill badges only. Sharp corners forbidden for interactive surfaces.

## Components

Component tokens reference primitives via `{path.to.token}` — never hardcode colors at the component level. Variants for state (hover, active, disabled) suffix the component name with the state.

## Do's and Don'ts

- Do use the primary color for the single most important action per screen.
- Don't mix rounded and sharp corners in the same view.
- Do maintain WCAG AA contrast for all text.
- Don't use more than two font families on a single screen.
